main event: An unidentified visual object was sighted near Baltimore, Maryland on September 21, 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as three objects in the form of a triangle, with the point of the triangle moving towards the southwest. Two of the objects were white in color and one was green.
The objects were accompanied by a triangular shape similar to a jet aircraft, but lower in pitch.
The white objects were about the size of a nickel, and the green object was about the size of a dime.
The objects were in sight for approximately 1 minute and moved at a speed of around 180 knots.
The observation was made by a high school student, but the reliability and experience of the observer was unknown.
